==English==

===Etymology 1===

From [[scum]].

====Noun====

'''scumming'''

# (printers' jargon) The accumulation of sticky ink on a [[plate]].

===Etymology 2===

Probably from [[skim|skimming]], modified by the derogatory sense of [[scum]].

====Noun====

'''scumming'''

# (''gamers' jargon'') The strategy of collecting easy rewards in unchallenging areas, e.g. when a high-level character visits levels suitable for low-level characters in [[w:Roguelike|roguelike]] games.
# (''gamers' jargon'') The act of restoring a game's save file for the purpose of continuing play with a better outcome than was obtained the first time.

====Derived terms====

# stair scumming, town scumming
# save-scumming, save-file scumming
# auto-scumming

